This directory contains local ArgoCD manifest examples generated from `app.yaml`.
`k8s-forge` does not install ArgoCD, does not push Git commits, does not create credentials, does not apply manifests, and does not synchronize applications automatically.

## What GitOps Means Here

GitOps means a Git repository holds the desired state. ArgoCD reads that repository, compares the desired state with the cluster, and can synchronize differences when an operator chooses to do so.

The generated `Application` points ArgoCD at a Helm chart path in Git:

```text
{{ gitops.source.repo_url }}
{{ gitops.source.target_revision }}
{{ gitops.source.path }}
```

## Generated Files

- `argocd/application.yaml`: namespace-scoped ArgoCD `Application` manifest.

